A **personal loan** is an unsecured loan — no collateral required — making it the most accessible credit product. However, the higher risk results in higher interest rates: typically 11–24% p.a. depending on your credit score, income, and lender. Understanding the total interest cost before taking a personal loan is critical to avoid a debt trap.
